==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[consumere]]''

===Pronunciation===
*(''UK''): {{IPA|/kənˈsjuːm/}}, {{SAMPA|/k@n"sju:m/}}
*(''US''): {{AHD|kən-so͞om}}, {{IPA|/kənˈsuːm/}}, {{SAMPA|/k@n"su:m/}}
*{{audio|en-us-consume.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|consum|ing}}

#{{transitive}} To [[use]].
#:''The power plant '''consumes''' 30 tons of coal per hour.''
#{{transitive}} To [[eat]].
#{{transitive}} To [[occupy]] (one’s attention or thoughts). 
#:''Desire '''consumed''' him.''
#{{transitive}} To [[destroy]] completely.
#:''The building was consumed by fire.''

====Synonyms====
*(''use''): [[burn]] (''of energy''), [[use]], [[use up]]
